SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 832
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to recognize Randy Elliott on the occasion of his
retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
honor those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout
their years of public service; and
WHEREAS, Randy Elliott is one such estimable person, who, after ten years of devoted
service to BrightStone, will take his much-deserved retirement; and
WHEREAS, in 2016, Mr. Elliott joined the team at BrightStone and served as Director of
Advancement, in which role he brought awareness to the organization's mission of loving and
serving others through faith and partnership and encouraged others to walk alongside
BrightStone in building innovative programs for adults with intellectual and developmental
disabilities; and
WHEREAS, Randy Elliott most recently served BrightStone as Chief of Staff, supporting
organizational leadership, governance, and strategic initiatives and remaining focused on
strengthening funding, community support, and long-range planning to ensure the organization
can faithfully serve families now and for generations to come; and
WHEREAS, during his distinguished tenure, Mr. Elliott launched the Homecoming
Capital Campaign to support future residential expansion and growth; additionally, he supported
the Board of Directors in advancing state legislation to designate BrightStone as the state's pilot
residential program, affirming the nonprofit's innovative campus model and establishing a
framework for residential services unique to Middle Tennessee; and
SJR0832
013479
- 1 -

WHEREAS, through Mr. Elliott's leadership of the Land of Dreams Capital Campaign,
the Stinnett Center for Learning, Art, and Enterprise, and the first two residential homes on the
organization's current campus were brought to life; and
WHEREAS, prior to his work at BrightStone, Mr. Elliott held other key leadership roles,
including Director of Advancement at New Hope Academy; Director of Development at
Guideposts Foundation; President of Texas State Credit Company; and Vice President of
Thomas Nelson Publishers, in which role he excelled for seventeen years; and
WHEREAS, a leader in his community, Mr. Elliott served the Forrest Crossing
Community Homeowners Association Board as treasurer for four years and the Planned Giving
Council of Middle Tennessee Board as a member; he currently serves as treasurer and member
of the Parish Council at his church; and
WHEREAS, Randy Elliott earned his Bachelor of Arts degree in Journalism from the
University of Memphis; and
WHEREAS, his many professional accomplishments aside, Mr. Elliott is most grateful for
the love and support he shares with his wife, Ann; he is the proud father of four children and
grandfather of seven grandchildren; and
WHEREAS, throughout his exemplary tenure at BrightStone, Randy Elliott has
demonstrated the utmost professionalism, ability, and integrity, winning the unbridled respect
and admiration of his colleagues and community alike; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we extend to Randy Elliott our heartfelt wishes for a
happy and fulfilling retirement and every continued success in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
